description.narrative:
to ensure that quality data from unconnected countries and places, related to the
COVID-19 pandemic, with knowledge institutions in the lead, are available for Ministries
of Health, their Taskforces, public and private stakeholders in the health sector.
This project will be implemented in Ethiopia, Uganda and Zimbabwe.
The sub-objectives are to:
1. Help prepare Ministries of Health and Institutions for the pandemic;
2. Ensure that universities and institutions with medical data have capacities to assist the
navigation of the crisis with quality data;
3. Develop the systems on which to run the data-analytics;
4. Ensure that data-stewardship is carried out under strict adherence to the governance and
regulatory framework of the country and institution where the data belong;
5. Enable data to be analyzed in relation to data available globally;

-	Urban poor and IDPs that are living in informal or relocation sites; 
-	Isolated island and coastal populations
-	Social workers and Front-liners

1 125 bénéficiaires primaires : filles et garçons non scolarisés identifiés ; 
- 10.000 bénéficiaires secondaires : autres élèves des écoles ciblées qui bénéficieront indirectement des actions entreprises dans les 25 écoles ciblées ;
- 77043  élèves qui bénéficient les émissions radio 
- 77043élèves qui bénéficient le matériel scolaire
- enseignants en charge de ces écoles.
